http://localhost:8081/actuator/health


to check if the service is up and running. You should see a response indicating the status of the service, such as "UP" or "DOWN". If the service is running properly, you can proceed to test the message sending functionality by making a POST request to the appropriate endpoint with the required parameters.

http://localhost:8081/messages

To verify that the Message Service is running correctly, you can use the following endpoint.

{
  "conversationId": "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
  "senderId": "22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222",
  "content": "Hello Distributed Worl"
}

You can use the body above to send a test message. If the service is functioning correctly, you should receive a successful response indicating that the message has been sent.# Message Service

docker exec -it kafka kafka-console-consumer --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic chat-messages --from-beginning

This command allows you to consume messages from the "chat-messages" topic in Kafka. By running this command, you can see the messages that have been sent to the topic, which can help you verify that the Message Service is working correctly and that messages are being produced as expected.